m
\sum_{j=1}^\ell d_j \le \ell(\ell-1) + \sum_{j=\ell+1}^{m-1}(d_j) + k
\sum_{j=1}^\ell d_j = m + \cdots + (m-\ell +1) = \frac{(2\ell)(2\ell+1)}{2} - \frac{(\ell + 1)(\ell)}{2}
\sum_{j=\ell+1}^{m-1}(d_j) = (m-\ell) + \cdots + 2 = \frac{(\ell + 1)(\ell)}{2} - 1
\frac{(2\ell)(2\ell+1)}{2} - \frac{(\ell + 1)(\ell)}{2} - \frac{(\ell + 1)(\ell)}{2} + 1 - \ell(\ell-1) \le k
\ell(2\ell + 1) - (\ell-1)\ell - (\ell + 1)\ell + 1 \le k
\ell + 1 = \frac{2\ell+2}{2} = \left\lfloor\frac{m + 3}{2}\right\rfloor\le k
